race.comment: SNITZEL MISS (10) settled a fair way off the pace before lengthening nicely in the run home to finish fourth when resuming over 1200m at Rosehill last start. Should travel a bit closer this time from a better gate. Placed in the Group 2 Sweet Embrace second-up last prep which is gilt-edged form for a midweek maiden. OUR HUNTRESS (8) was popular with punters but was edged out on debut over 1200m at Kembla 24 days ago. Clark should have her up near the speed and another bold run is anticipated. JAEGERS (5) led and battled on well for second (SNITZEL MISS fourth) at Rosehill recently. Very fast filly who can neutralise the wide draw. Blinkers going on an interesting move - she probably looks the winner at some stage. LAMBERTINA (6) gets a pass-mark for her debut effort at Gosford. Likely improver. KONSA (1)
